  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "Composition is the operation of combining two functions so that the output of the first becomes the input of the second. Given a function f:A→Bf : A \\to B and a function g:B→Cg : B \\to C, their composition g∘fg \\circ f is a new function from AA to CC that applies ff first, then gg to the result:\n(g∘f)(x)=g(f(x)) (g \\circ f)(x) = g(f(x)) Composition is the primary mechanism by which functional programming builds complex behavior from simple parts. Rather than writing a single large function, a functional programmer writes small pure functions and wires them together through composition.\n",
